The evidence with the title 'Dangers of CFL Mercury Light Bulbs ' says (by comparison, old-style mercury thermometers contain about 500 milligrams of mercury , an amount equal to the mercury found in 125 cfl bulbs.) And, provided the bulbs are n't broken open, none of that leaches into the home. Like batteries, used CFLs need to be disposed at atoxic waste depot rather than tossed out  ... 
